The river drains an area of 5460 km² and in 1997 had an annual discharge of 135.4 m³/s or 4.3 km³ per year. The Phum Duang River (or Khirirat River), which drains another 6,125 km² west of the Tapi watershed, joins the estuary 15 km west of Surat Thani in Amphoe Phunphin.

The river was named in August 1915 after the river Tapi in India, shortly after the town of Surat Thani was named after the town Surat.-->

